  <eligibility>
    <criteria>
      <textblock>
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  Patients in the Critical Care Unit on veno-arterial ECMO.

          -  Hemodynamic stability established, as adjudged by the treating CCU staff physician.

          -  Informed consent by parent or legal guardian.

          -  Approval by treating CCU staff physician to approach parents/guardians for consent
             process at any given time.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  Patients in the Critical Care Unit on veno-venous (VV) ECMO.

          -  Inability to tolerate study period without red cell transfusion.

          -  Presence of a large leak around the endotracheal tube (&gt; 10% tidal volume).

          -  Patients requiring &gt; 70 % FiO2 at the time of potential enrollment.

          -  Parent or legal guardian refuse consent.
      </textblock>
    </criteria>
